<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    ROGUE secret!</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:noisy@mindspring.com">Constance IN Bertoxxulous</a> | 
		            5/31/1999 6:54:51 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">If you take on the hard life of a Rogue,  you must know the rogue-merchant secret!<BR>
Most merchant will not sell to a rogue... something about reputation or character. Well, what the merchant doesn't know won't hurt them!  Go behind a merchant (out of their line of sight) and use the sneak skill...<BR>
then click on the merchant, and they will sell to you/buy from you without ever knowing you're a rogue!  Enjoy!<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
