	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Alrighty all.  This is the least known and by far the most valuable skill to figure out and use correctly.  It will increase your damage dealing by a ton, and save your life when things are close to the line.<BR>
<BR>
EVADE:<BR>
1.  What do I push?  Well evade for rogues works with the &quot;HIDE&quot; button.<BR>
2.  When can I use?  The only time this will work for you is when the mob that you are actively fighting is also being attacked by another PC.<BR>
3.  How do I make it work?  Hit your auto attack button (click it off) and click &quot;hide&quot;.<BR>
4.  What does it do?  Usually automatically makes the mob turn and attack the highest damage making PC that is currently attacking it.  Esentually a reverse &quot;taunt&quot;, except you benefit.<BR>
5.  Why use this?  Because now you can BS twice as many times.  Or you can get out of battle when your hitpoints are getting low.<BR>
6.  Best uses I've found?  Well there are many.  When in a group with one one or two magics this is useful to extend the &quot;quick&quot; damage potential of group.  At lvl 16, I was able to BS for 41, hit for 12 and 12, 12 and 12, 12 and 12 (dual wield and not mentioning the obsidian shard proc damage) and when my BS lit up again I evaded and BS for another 41.  So within 10 seconds I am able to generate in the ball park (and without proc damage) 130 points of damage...CONSISTENTLY.<BR>
7.  Hazards?  Careful of your magic user partners.  If you are grouped with a Wiz or other high damage wielding dd specialist.  It will be tough to draw the attention back to you with your BS...so you may want to only consider using this talent when you have an armored class recieving the blows while you're evading.<BR>
8.  Final thought:  I believe strongly that if anyone has a problem with these phylosophies on rogue combat I can justify using them with one word....ROGUE....we are rogues....shady characters that are out for ourselves.  It should be a privaledge for other classes to reap the reward of battling with such a mighty damage dealer.  In more cases than not I can deal out nearly twice the amount of damage that a warriro of the same lvl can deal and that is as described about (without the twink procs).  They must also take some to the risk, and by this I mean be willing to recieve a blow or two from a mob so you can maximize the groups damage potential with your BS.  So walk with pride rogues.  BS / EVADE / BS / EVADE..... you will be the envy of all.  
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
